    "(2) Canonical: The difficulty is adjusted based on all blocks in the canonical chain.Ledger Function.",
    "The ledger function determines the content of the ledger: which transactions are considered valid and net fees to the miner who included them.We consider the two following ledger functions.",
    "(1) Canonical: The ledger is the concatenation of all blocks in the canonical chain.",
    "(2) MAD: The ledger is the concatenation of all non-destructed blocks in the canonical chain.Colordag uses the uncontested difficulty-adjustment mechanism.",
    "While it doesn't specify its exact ledger function, the canonical ledger function is a natural choice."
